==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|Florence|lang=fr}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|Florentia|lang=la}} ( as a given name, a feminine form of {{term|Florentius|lang=la}}), from {{term|florens||flowering, flourishing|lang=la}}.
* The female given name gained popularity from [[w:Florence Nightingale|Florence Nightingale]] who was born in the Tuscan city

